Q2. Monitor & Verify Files [15 Marks]
1. Enable Logging
bash
# Edit /etc/ssh/sshd_config
LogLevel VERBOSE

sudo systemctl restart ssh
# View logs
sudo tail -f /var/log/auth.log | grep sftp
2. Check File Integrity
Before transfer (on source):

bash
sha256sum file.txt > file.txt.sha256
After transfer (on destination):

bash
sha256sum -c file.txt.sha256
# Output: file.txt: OK
3. Scan for Malware
bash
# Install ClamAV
sudo apt install clamav -y
sudo freshclam

# Scan uploads folder
clamscan /home/sftpuser/uploads/
